<subSubSection id="C1826517072FFF80FF33FE1A6F0F4450" pageId="3" pageNumber="237" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8927369C072FFF80FF33FE1A6F0F4450" blockId="3.[189,1396,286,712]" pageId="3" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis id="BBECEA8E072FFF80FF33FE1A69104406" bold="true" box="[192,543,483,516]" pageId="3" pageNumber="237">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. Five subspecies of the Western Pocket 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F072FFF80FD8BFDF269EA442E" box="[632,741,523,556]" class="Reptilia" family="Testudinidae" genus="Gopher" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="3" pageNumber="237" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gopher</taxonomicName>
(glacialis, pugetensis, tumuli, and yelmensis) are classified as threatened by the US Fish and Wildlife Service.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
